Miyazaki’s own films reflect his taste: he has Norstein’s flair for mythmaking, Back’s sensitivity to nature, Ozu’s feel for family life, Mizoguchi’s compassion for women. (Miyazaki’s most complex characters tend to be headstrong girls between the ages of 5-11.) And like the Neorealists, his stories are always relevant, however far-fetched.
